<http://www.spektrix.com/tidemarktheatre/event/55001AMSBLSDPDNMRVSMJKRHLNGCNQBMH>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Crash Test Dummies";
  schema:description """
	With one of the most recognizable voices in Canadian music, Crash Test Dummies return to the Tidemark Theatre on November 12th with their <span class=\"ItalicText\">Jingle All the Way</span> holiday tour.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Rising to international fame in the early ’90s, the band made their mark with hits like Mmm, Mmm, Mmm, Mmm and Superman’s Song, songs that still resonate decades later thanks to their distinctive sound and the unmistakable baritone of Brad Roberts. Blending folk influences with alternative rock, their live show leans into what they do best: thoughtful songwriting, tight musicianship, and a sound that’s instantly familiar but never dated.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Expect a mix of fan favourites, seasonal touches, and the kind of understated, powerful performance that has kept audiences coming back for over 30 years.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Opening the night is Logan Richard, a rising East Coast artist whose sound moves easily between blues, folk, pop, and soul. Known for his smooth vocals and impressive guitar work, the PEI-based musician has spent years performing across Canada both as a solo artist and alongside some of the country’s top musicians. His latest album, Character Traits, highlights his versatility as a songwriter while bringing a fresh, modern edge to classic singer-songwriter storytelling.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Tickets: $57 Admission <span class=\"ItalicText\">(+applicable taxes & fees)</span>
""";
  schema:startDate "2026-11-12T19:30:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
  schema:image <https://system.spektrix.com/tidemarktheatre/files/50280ef1-9f67-4bf9-884c-4f18e7c91a54.jpg>;
  schema:location <https://spektrix.com/tidemarktheatre/location/405AGDKDKNLGVLJCSNTLQBVTRTGBTHCPJ>;
  schema:url <https://tidemarktheatre.com/event/crash-test-dummies/>;
  schema:offers _:cab21ce75f7f43899f29f24336be7ed88710;
  schema:duration "PT120M";
  schema:endDate "2026-11-12T21:30:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

_:cab21ce75f7f43899f29f24336be7ed88710 a schema:AggregateOffer;
  schema:lowPrice "60.0";
  schema:priceCurrency "CAD" .

<http://www.spektrix.com/tidemarktheatre/event/31401ACGSQBSNGJMMSMSJDBKPVTCCSKMC>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Fleetwood Magic";
  schema:description """
	Fleetwood Magic Tribute Show masterfully transports audiences in sound and time through a musical journey performing Fleetwood Mac’s greatest hits from the 60’s to the 80’s, authentically recreating the sound, style and mystique of Fleetwood Mac’s most iconic line-up. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>With stunning vintage costumes, precise vocals, period-accurate instrumentation, and captivating on-stage personas, Fleetwood Magic delivers a live experience that reminds fans why Fleetwood Mac remains legendary.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Relive timeless classics like “Rhiannon,” “Dreams,” “You Make Loving Fun,” “Say You Love Me,” “The Chain,” “Go Your Own Way.” Listeners have come to realize the <span class=\"ItalicText\">'Rumours'</span> are true – Fleetwood Magic does indeed, deliver the magic! <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Consistently playing sold out shows to audiences across the Vancouver Lower Mainland and Canada, their shows have become a must-see event for Fleetwood Mac music fans of all ages!<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>For more information about Fleetwood Magic, please visit: <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.fleetwoodmagic.ca\">www.fleetwoodmagic.ca</a><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Tickets: $59 Admission, Groups of 6+ Receive 10% off <span class=\"ItalicText\">(+applicable taxes & fees)</span><span><br/></span>
""";
  schema:startDate "2026-09-18T19:30:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
